depressive picture of online interaction today, in the past, and
for the future. People have no idea what to believe as politics have
spread into matters they had no business in, promoting
misinformation to support their lobbyists and political platform.
More and more people are falling into online echo chambers of
people reverberating the same, often problematic ideas, and nobody
If anything, websites, news outlets, etc. are cashing in on this.
Using the drama to retain users and generate revenue from
advertising. In short, this situation is "ingrained in the mainframe,"
but what if it wasnt. Thats what led to bigolworld being ideated,
